The paper deals with the application of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) to learn decryption algorithms for polyalphabetic ciphers. This falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques such as RNNs, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the efficiency of the RNNs in learning algorithmic tasks, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves the use of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) cells, which are a type of neural network architecture commonly used in the field of neural engineering (cs.NE).
